commit_message:
Align the stars to unblock instack-undercloud gate on stable/mitaka

We need to squash to patches if we want to unblock stable/mitaka CI.

First patch:

Fix bashate errors and warnings (lint)

Fix 1 warning and 1 error in bash syntax:

1) E043: Arithmetic compound has inconsistent return semantics.
   Fix the bash syntax to be compliant.

2) ERROR: Split export and assignments in 2 files. Ignore the files.
   Fix the bash syntax to be compliant.
   Note: this test has been introducted by
   https://review.openstack.org/#/c/400542/

(cherry picked from commit 9031dcf62016c5ca198a39109425b9f063e131fc)

Second Patch:

Run `yum update -y` before Puppet run

This patch run `yum update -y` right before running os-refresh-config
(Puppet).

1) Running `yum` from an Exec in Puppet is a bad idea because Puppet has
no idea which packages resources are touched, so we're loosing the
orchestration control.

2) We need to ensure that `yum update -y` runs before any attempt to
deploy OpenStack services, so we have latest packages from RDO and
CentOS.

Closes-Bug: #1650374
(cherry picked from commit 853b4bfbadda67cf659a8a744b82d128a4bc3247)

Change-Id: Ifbbbdbf1f0c569791abc712913c7e0f6bbe533d9
(cherry picked from commit aab2dadd199a57042274a7f8771dc1774be85399)

commit_message:
Implement NFS multi backend support

The NFS implementation based off cinder_nfs_client
does not support per cinder backend configuration,
separating NFS mounts per backend.
This fix removes cinder_nfs_client in favor of
fully supporting multi cinder backends over the
cinder_backends stanza.

Closes-Bug #1657203

Change-Id: I817ff372c2d58e999a89496fce3d25dc617216f0

commit_message:
Extract /etc from subnode logs for easy browser viewing

Add the full contents of /etc from each subnode into the exploded etc
dir in the logs directory. This will make the full contents of etc more

subject: Handle RETRY_LIMIT failure type in cistatus script
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-01-23 15:33:34.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/tripleo-jobs-gerrit.py'], 'message': 'Handle RETRY_LIMIT failure type in cistatus script

A normal Jenkins message about a job status looks like:
gate-tripleo-ci-centos-7-ovb-ha SUCCESS in 1h 49m 28s

A RETRY_LIMIT message looks like:
gate-tripleo-ci-centos-7-ovb-nonha RETRY_LIMIT

Because we get the duration from this message, the latter causes us
issues parsing the message.  This change makes that code handle
the case where there is no time included.

Change-Id: Ieb75e6dc43fb6fb4c8b86f399a23cd26978ba7d2
'}]
commit_message:
Handle RETRY_LIMIT failure type in cistatus script

A normal Jenkins message about a job status looks like:
gate-tripleo-ci-centos-7-ovb-ha SUCCESS in 1h 49m 28s

A RETRY_LIMIT message looks like:
gate-tripleo-ci-centos-7-ovb-nonha RETRY_LIMIT

Because we get the duration from this message, the latter causes us
issues parsing the message.  This change makes that code handle
the case where there is no time included.

Change-Id: Ieb75e6dc43fb6fb4c8b86f399a23cd26978ba7d2

commit_message:
Pecan: normalize req urls; handle double slashes

The legacy framework loaded the app using paste deploy.  This wrapped
the app with paste.urlmap.URLMap and caused all incoming requests to hae
their url's normalized, which handled double slashes.

Change-Id: I751999a46680c3db908cf48fe9d204cf034c83e7

subject: catch SElinux alerts in permissive mode
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2017-01-23 17:27:05.000000000', 'files': ['run_tests.sh'], 'message': 'catch SElinux alerts in permissive mode

Run the tests in permissive mode but run sealert at the end to see if we
have some SElinux alerts that we need to fix.

We want to run catch_selinux_alerts function before exiting the script
(with failure or success) so we can detect alerts:
* right after first Puppet run
* after second Puppet run
* after Tempest run

If an AVC is detected, fails so we can report the bugs in
openstack-selinux and bring useful feedback.

Change-Id: Iaef45c88232505600cbb80f82b195aafcc615474
(cherry picked from commit 982f18c2820092fd67715c7f96b0ac816a44203c)
'}]
commit_message:
catch SElinux alerts in permissive mode

Run the tests in permissive mode but run sealert at the end to see if we
have some SElinux alerts that we need to fix.

We want to run catch_selinux_alerts function before exiting the script
(with failure or success) so we can detect alerts:
* right after first Puppet run
* after second Puppet run
* after Tempest run

If an AVC is detected, fails so we can report the bugs in
openstack-selinux and bring useful feedback.

Change-Id: Iaef45c88232505600cbb80f82b195aafcc615474
(cherry picked from commit 982f18c2820092fd67715c7f96b0ac816a44203c)

commit_message:
Add THT for fossw ML2 plugin in networking-fujitsu

Introduce THT for fossw ML2 plugin in networking-fujitsu.
networking-fujitsu is a neutron ML2 plugin which enables several
FUJITSU switch products in OpenStack environment. This templates
deploy overcloud with FOS switch.

Change-Id: I977dbecbf9f6f9725f7fb5ca4745b537a73975ff

commit_message:
Add manila-manage db purge command

Cloud admins delete lots of DB records manually that were
"soft-deleted" in Manila. They do it to reduce size of DB
and increase response speed. Therefore, add "manila-manage
db purge" command that will make cloud admins life easier
allowing them to purge such DB records in one click.

Examples of usage:
$ manila-manage db purge 5

Partially-implements: blueprint clean-deleted-row-in-db
Depends-on: 0ec71e29b2f0b817fe7c4fcdcf1918c2eff811a0
Change-Id: I4fd83d44f4a1b6b7633a60249ba775f6d86d1cdc

commit_message:
Allow for specifying the output_dir

Allow for passing the output_dir in the process-templates scripts so
that it doesn't overwrites the templates in the src dir. This is a
desired feature when running the script from a t-h-t installed
system-wide.

Change-Id: I47994d34f47a4084a11124bc9075cb2f457889ea

Ignore hidden files in directories

commit_message:
Clarify that octavia-db-manage should be used

It was not clear to users that we now use octavia-db-manage for
alembic actions in octavia.  Users would get an exception if they
tried to use native alembic due to changes to the env.py.
This patch updates the README.rst and env.py to clarify that
octavia-db-manage should be used.

Change-Id: I97e7fce5da167875694bc1a6abc69d47b3021487

Problem, if a user has old source in OPT_WORKDIR they
may not have the ansible_ssh_env.sh file and quickstart will fail.
I consider this a temporary fix until we either add traps
or change the default clone behavior of quickstart as this
can happen in other cases.

commit_message:
warn user regarding old src in $OPT_WORKDIR

Problem, if a user has old source in OPT_WORKDIR they
may not have the ansible_ssh_env.sh file and quickstart will fail.
I consider this a temporary fix until we either add traps
or change the default clone behavior of quickstart as this
can happen in other cases.
Neither of the ideal fixes are small changes and a warning should be
raised to the user to run with --clean in the meantime.

Change-Id: I47fc30188793b09034829405a59e1dd2f4328796

commit_message:
Allow blank rabbit password if using transport_url

rabbit_password was deprecated as part of
Idb4b53f7149d8867f92e5053b6557cd1f1a4b24f and transport_url should be
used instead. However if you use transport_url, it would fail if you
did not also provide the rabbit_password. We should not fail for a blank
rabbit_password if transport_url is used.

Change-Id: I00d4782693c1f67b82673624d4d36822c9762303
(cherry picked from commit d4e3055b38d69db41afccf6ed2ffe6dea9cf6645)

commit_message:
Add DIB_IPA_COMPRESS_CMD option

This option allows to specifiy command for compress built initramfs image
for ironic-agent element. This command can be specified with arguments and
should read raw data from stdin and write compressed data to stdout.
Default if "gzip".

Change-Id: I0fdd2ab91d7bf7aaaa6cdd5278e3902d44c5b883

Prior to splitting out the overcloud roles, deploying with instructions

commit_message:
Update the README to return the deploy with instructions to previous functionality

Prior to splitting out the overcloud roles, deploying with instructions
meant that all the scripts and configuration required to deploy the
overcloud were included on the overcloud.  The updated command returns
that ability to the instructions.   The undercloud is installed and all
the scripts required for an overcloud deployment are available on the
undercloud.

commit_message:
Enable systemd service which disables smt

Systemd service for disabling smt on ppc64le compute nodes was added
earlier. But the service is not enabled. So after reboot, smt is
not getting disabled on ppc64le compute nodes. This patch adds
code to enable the smt-disabling systemd service.

Change-Id: I0b0371f97aa56a190cd6622b7ade739efc7c98f2

commit_message:
WIP Add notifications for resource providers

A notification will be sent when resource providers are created,
destroyed, updated, associated with an aggregate and disassociated
with an aggregate.

Thus far this sends a very simple whitelisted, non-versioned
notification after a create. There's a lot more to do.

Todo:

* figure out notification contents
* create versioned notification
* determine if we need create.{start,end} or if create by itself is
  sufficient
* add notifications (and tests) for each type described above
* notifications on inventory changes
* notifications on allocations?

Change-Id: I3cdcf397037c56a1c3cf9915096d3d7e15ac0695
Partially-Implements: blueprint generic-resource-pools

If we crate the vnfd using the command:
$ tacker vnfd-create --name <vnfd-name> --vnfd-file=<file-name>

commit_message:
Fix vnfd-create error: Invalid input for name

If we crate the vnfd using the command:
$ tacker vnfd-create --name <vnfd-name> --vnfd-file=<file-name>

then it throws the following error:
Invalid input for name. Reason: 'True' is not a valid string.

because after parsing the command line argument again the name
parameter is getting overwritten by the "_extra-values".

Change-Id: Ie7105e004e92cd7dab912c810757a113f2dc898a
Signed-off-by: subhash kumar singh <subh.singh007@gmail.com>
